18 September 2019 - Elsies River residents comfort one another following a shooting in which four people were killed and two were wounded. 18 September 2019 - A dance trophy lies in the ruins of a Khuma councillor's house in the North West. Six ANC councillor's houses were set alight in service delivery protests. 18 September 2019 - President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses a joint sitting of parliament because "a dark and heavy shadow is hanging across the land. Women and girls are under siege". 18 September 2019 - The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) is addressed by the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) about cases involving the SABC.